HEADWORD: Totipalmate
<hw>To`ti*pal"mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>totus</ets> all, whole + E. <ets>palmate</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having all four toes united by a web; -- said of
certain sea birds, as the pelican and the gannet. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
under <er>Aves</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Totipalmi</ent>⟦br⟧
